. In this work, we present a new method for deep neural network classification that is based on using the neural network to model the object of interest. We show that our method can be successfully used to classify objects of interest in the real world. The proposed method is able to achieve a classification accuracy of > 95% and a classification accuracy of > 97.5% when using a sample of 100 objects.

We present a comprehensive approach to adversarial robustness and review our results and propose a novel, easy-to-use approach to achieving high-quality adversarial robustness through the use of multi-resolution input representations and dynamic self-ensembling of intermediate layer predictions. Our approach has significant potential to improve the robustness of deep neural networks and is a promising tool for developing adversarial robustness in deep learning.
